    {
      "para_id": "Q001092.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Inana and Lugal-emuš , En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , built the E-muš , their beloved temple , and embellished it with inscribed clay nails ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001092.9",
      "line_range": "9",
      "translation": "(i 9) The personal god of En-metena , the builder of the E-muš , is Šul-MUŠxPA ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001092.13",
      "line_range": "13",
      "translation": "(ii 4) At that time En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , and Lugal-kiĝeneš-dudu , ruler of Unug , established brotherhood ."
    }
  ],
